 result‚Üêobject extent arg;size;extent;where;dthick;Borders;margins;t;tunits;punits;dysize;resize;pscale;scale;pxsize;mdi
‚çù Request or modify the size of a GUI object

‚çù Note: 'where' is outside dimensions, relative to parent and using parent's scale
‚çù       'size' is inside (client area) dimensions, less internal margins, using current scale
‚çù       'extent' is inside (client area) dimensions, but using parent's scale
‚çù While object is closed:
‚çù       Assign where‚Üê2‚ç¥ leaves it as 2‚ç¥ and doesn't change size/extent
‚çù       Assign where‚Üê4‚ç¥ changes size/extent to ‚ç¨
‚çù       Assign size‚Üê2‚ç¥ or extent‚Üê2‚ç¥, truncates where to 2‚ç¥
‚çù       Scale‚â†0 just doesn't store elements #2-#5
‚çù       Upon opening, all are resynchronized ‚çù? Do we need to do this?

 arg‚Üê##.Single arg ‚çù Make sure a nested argument is disclosed
 '‚àÜWI DOMAIN ERROR: extent'##.Error~##.IsNum arg
 '‚àÜWI RANK ERROR: extent'##.Error 1<‚â¢‚ç¥arg

 :Select ‚â¢arg

 :Case 0
     result‚Üêobject ‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_extent'‚ç¨ ‚çù Where is it currently located?

 :Case 2
     '‚àÜWI DOMAIN ERROR: extent'##.Error‚à®/0>arg
     :Section ‚çù Get all our basic information
         (where extent size scale)‚Üêobject ‚éïVGET('_where'‚ç¨)('_extent'‚ç¨)('_size'‚ç¨)('_scale' 1) ‚çù My current settings
         pscale‚Üê(‚äÉobject._Ancestry)‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_scale' 1 ‚çù Parent's scale (for use by where and extent)
         (tunits punits)‚Üê2‚Üë_supp.MyUnits object
         Borders‚Üê_supp.GetBorders object ‚çù Time to figure out what the border definitions are for this class (capitalized because it represents a global)
         resize‚Üêsize ‚çù Remember this
     :EndSection

     :Section ‚çù Recompute APL+Win 'extent'
         extent‚Üêarg ‚çù We'd better just be able to assign this
         margins‚Üê+/2 2‚ç¥+‚åøBorders[1;,2;] ‚çù Differences between 'extent' and 'size' (in pixels)
         pxsize‚Üê‚åä0.5+margins-‚ç®extent√ópunits ‚çù Recompute pxsize, rescaling as needed
     :EndSection
     :Section ‚çù Recompute APL+Win 'where'
         margins‚Üê+/2 2‚ç¥+‚åøBorders[1;1 3;] ‚çù Differences between 'extent' and 'where' (in pixels)
         where‚Üê(2‚Üëwhere),extent+margins√∑punits ‚çù We'll just compute the new size for 'where', using a common scale
     :EndSection
     :Section ‚çù Recompute APL+Win 'size'
         :If 0‚â†‚äÉscale ‚çù If we're in proportional scaling, we don't change 'size' at all
             margins‚Üê+/2 2‚ç¥+‚åøBorders[1;,2;] ‚çù Differences between 'extent' and 'size' (in pixels)
             size‚Üêtunits√∑‚ç®margins-‚ç®extent√ópunits ‚çù Recompute 'size', rescaling as needed
         :EndIf
     :EndSection
     :Section ‚çù Set APL+Win properties
         :If scale‚äÉ‚çõ‚àä5 6 ‚ãÑ size‚Üê‚åä0.5+size ‚ãÑ :EndIf ‚çù If 'scale' is in pixels, round to integers
         :If pscale‚äÉ‚çõ‚àä5 6 ‚ãÑ (where extent)‚Üê‚åä0.5+where extent ‚ãÑ :EndIf ‚çù If parent 'scale' is in pixels, round to integers
         object.(_where _size _extent _pix_size)‚Üêwhere size extent pxsize ‚çù Set new APL+Win reference values
‚çù? Make adjustments for closed object handling
     :EndSection
     :Section ‚çù Compute and set Dyalog positioning properties
         dysize‚Üê(extent√ópunits)+_supp.GetSizes object
         :If 'User'‚â°object ##.‚àÜWGet‚äÇ'Coord' 'Prop' ‚çù In this case, we've got to do something about using custom coordinates (used for Pictures)
             ##.Halt'How do we need to handle this??'
             ‚çù? How can I relocate the Picture parent when its Coord=User? Does it use the parent's Coord?
             ‚çù? What happens if there's a Picture within a Picture?
         :EndIf
         object ##.‚àÜWSet‚äÇ'Size'dysize
         :If ‚éïNULL‚â†mdi‚Üêobject ‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_mdi'‚éïNULL ‚çù If there's an MDI Client area here, resize it too
         :AndIf 0=‚â¢mdi ‚éïVGET‚äÇ'_clientwhere'‚ç¨ ‚çù If it's using automatic sizing
             mdi ##.‚àÜWSet‚äÇ'Size'dysize
         :EndIf
     :EndSection

     :If size‚â¢resize ‚çù Only if the size is changing
